		<br>

		<div style="text-align:right ; padding-right:70px;font-size: 11pt;">
{!CASE(MONTH(TODAY()),1, "January",2, "February",3, "March", 4, "April", 5, "May", 6,"June",7, "July",8, "August",9, "September",10, "October",11, "November",12, "December","None")} {!TEXT(DAY(TODAY()))}, {!TEXT(YEAR(TODAY()))}
</div>
		<br><br>
		<div style="font-size: 11pt;">
{!Product__c.First_Name__c} {!Product__c.Last_Name__c} <br>
			{!Product__c.Address_Line1__c}, {!Product__c.Address_Line2__c} <br>
			{!Product__c.City__c}, {!Product__c.State__c} <br>
			{!Product__c.Zip_Code__c} <br>
		</div>
		<br>
		<span style="font-size: 11pt;">Delivery Method:  Regular mail, cc email</span>
		<br><br>
		<div style="text-align:center; text-decoration:underline; margin-left:-24%;">Without Prejudice</div>
		<br><br>
		<strong>
		<span style="font-size: 11pt;"">RE: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {!Product__c.Product_Type_Display_Name__c} Number - {!Product__c.Name} <span><br>
			&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Current Balance: {!Product__c.Current_Balance__c}
        </strong><br><br>
        <hr style="border-top: 2px solid;></hr><br>

		<div style="width:96%; font-size: 11pt;">
			As you have already been made aware, your {!Product__c.Product_Type_Display_Name__c} is seriously delinquent. Despite our attempts to contact you to resolve this, you have not made a payment since {!CASE(MONTH(TODAY()),1, "January",2, "February",3, "March", 4, "April", 5, "May", 6,"June",7, "July",8, "August",9, "September",10, "October",11, "November",12, "December","None")} {!TEXT(DAY(TODAY()))}, {!TEXT(YEAR(TODAY()))} and your account balance remains outstanding.
		</div>
		<br>

		<div style="width:96%;  font-size: 11pt;">
			This letter is to advise that if payment in full is not received in our office<strong> within 10 days</strong> we will be initiating legal proceedings to recover the full balance owing. Please be advised that if a Claim is required to be issued against you we will be seeking all costs and applicable interest. Once the anticipated Judgment is obtained we will immediately report to your credit file and commence enforcement proceedings with no further notice. Additional enforcement can include any one or a combination of the following:
		</div>
		<br>
		<div style="width:96%;  font-size: 11pt;">
			<div style="width:95%; font-size: 11pt; padding-left:4%;">
				&#10146; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Registration</strong> of the Judgment against property you may own now or in the future.<br><br>
				&#10146;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Garnishment</strong> of up to 100% of your bank account until the Judgment has been satisfied.<br><br>

&#10146;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A Debtor Examination</strong> where you will be required to appear in Court and compelled to disclose all &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;relevant personal financial information.
			<div>
</div>
		</div><br>
		<span style=" font-size: 11pt;">Please conduct yourself appropriately.</span>
		<br>
        <div>
		<img src='https://c.na55.content.force.com/servlet/servlet.ImageServer?id=015f1000002kf5h&oid=00Dj0000001ripe&lastMod=1500029798000' style="width: 135px;padding-right: 15px;"/>
		</div>
		Affirm Financial Services <br>

		1-855-266-3131<br>
		<br><br>
		
		
		<span style="display: {!IF(Product__c.Product_Type_Display_Name__c == "Affirm Financial MasterCard", 'initial;', 'none;')}" >
		
			<div style="font-size: 11px;">
				If your records reflect that you paid this payment prior to the date of this email please contact us so that the discrepancy can be resolved and any necessary corrections made on your account. 
				Note that payments made using non-guaranteed funds may not create available credit on your account for up to 7 days to allow the payment to clear. Please see your Cardholder Agreement for the full terms on your account. You are receiving this email as per the agreed upon terms in your Cardholder Agreement.
			</div>
			<br>		
		
			<div style="text-align: center; background-color: #115995; color: #dbe3eb;font-size: 10px;padding: 4px;">
